Commenters may wish to specify whether qualitative information, including but not limited to the type described
above in Part I, is relevant to investors such that its disclosure should be encouraged. If so, should such information
be included in the safe harbor? Should forward-looking information that is currently part of required audited financial
information (such as loan-loss reserves, pension liabilities or contingent environmental liabilities) be included?

